\end_inset

 implies no shift in the BAO scale.
 We detect a significant shift (
\begin_inset Formula $\sim6\sigma$
\end_inset

 for most cases) for all the samples we consider.
 The shift is consistent with being constant for biases 
\begin_inset Formula $>$
\end_inset

 3.0 and only increases for extremely large biases.
 These results agree with the trends found in Ref.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
