\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Correlation between the redshift that the subhalos are accreted 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 (i.e., the redshift when the subhalos are accreted by their host halos) and
 the ratio of 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{{\rm vir,sub}}/M_{{\rm acc,sub}}$
\end_inset

 (left) and 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{{\rm max,sub}}/V_{{\rm acc,sub}}$
\end_inset

 (right) at 
\begin_inset Formula $z=0.3$
\end_inset

.
 Those figures indicate that subhalos which are accreted earlier tend to
 lose more masses, but the effect of tidal stripping on the change in potential
 well depth is less.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

